'''Kruuny''' was a [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] who was present on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Dubrillion/Legends|Dubrillion]]<ref name="Vector Prime" /> in [[25 ABY/Legends|25 ABY]]<ref name="ERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''</ref> at the beginning of the [[Yuuzhan Vong War|Yuuzhan Vong invasion]]. There, Kruuny piloted a [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] in the [[Battle of Dubrillion]] against the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] forces and struggled to shake the pursuit of enemy [[Yorik-et|coralskippers]]. After they voiced this struggle over the [[Comm unit/Legends|comm systems]], [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] cautioned the pilot to stay calm and assured them that [[Gender/Legends|he]] would assist in the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']]. Solo was true to his word and, acting as [[Gunner/Legends|gunner]], his [[Marriage/Legends|wife]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] eliminated the pursuing fighter with the ''Millennium Falcon''{{'s}} [[Quad laser cannon/Legends|quad laser cannons]]. Relieved after the close call, Kruuny thanked the [[Solo family/Legends|Solos]], an exchange that was overheard on the comms by the couple's three children, all of whom fought in the battle themselves.<ref name="Vector Prime" />

==Behind the scenes==
Kruuny first appeared in the [[1999]] novel ''[[The New Jedi Order: Vector Prime]]'' written by [[R. A. Salvatore]].<ref name="Vector Prime" />

